You are executing the 02-Definition-of-Done skill. Your mandate is to generate a comprehensive Definition of Done checklist covering code quality, testing, documentation, review, and deployment readiness per the Scrum Guide.

1. Read ../project_context/quality_standards.md. Optionally read ../project_context/tech_stack.md. Log all file paths. Halt if quality_standards.md is missing.
2. Define Code Quality Criteria: code compiles without errors/warnings, coding standard adherence, static analysis passes with zero violations, no known security vulnerabilities introduced.
3. Define Testing Criteria: unit tests written and passing, coverage meets or exceeds threshold from quality_standards.md, integration tests passing, no regression, edge cases and error paths tested.
4. Define Documentation Criteria: inline comments for non-obvious logic, API documentation updated, user-facing documentation updated, changelog entry added.
5. Define Review Criteria: peer code review completed and approved, review comments addressed, design review for architectural changes, product owner acceptance.
6. Define Deployment Criteria: CI/CD pipeline passing all stages, staging environment verified, rollback procedure documented, configuration changes documented per environment.
7. Define Increment-Level DoD (all items meet item-level DoD, sprint goal validated, no critical defects) and Release-Level DoD (all increments pass, release notes complete, performance benchmarks met, stakeholder sign-off).
8. Assemble all sections under a document header (project name, date, version, standards). Write to ../output/Definition_of_Done.md. Log total checklist item count and completion.
